title: Maia Sandu
added: Sandu announced her candidacy for the 2020 presidential election on 18 July<ref>{{Cite web|last=Gatcan|first=Diana|date=2020-07-18|title=Maia Sandu este candidata PAS la alegerile prezidențiale din noiembrie|url=https://www.zdg.md/importante/ultima-ora-maia-sandu-este-candidata-pas-la-alegerile-prezidentiale-din-noiembrie/|access-date=2020-11-16|website=Ziarul de Gardă|language=ro-RO}}</ref>, declaring that a joint [[Pro-Europeanism|pro-European]] candidate would not be needed as there was no risk of there being no pro-European candidates in the second round.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Maia Sandu: „Nu este atât de important să fie un candidat comun al dreptei pentru prezidențiale”|url=https://tv8.md/2020/05/13/maia-sandu-nu-este-atat-de-important-sa-fie-un-candidat-comun-al-dreptei-pentru-prezidentiale/|access-date=2020-11-16|language=ro-RO}}</ref> Sandu officially launched her campaign on 2 October 2020, holding 2 speeches in Romanian and Russian both promising to fight [[corruption]], [[poverty]] and to reform the [[Criminal justice|criminal justice system]].<ref>{{Cite web|last=|first=|date=2 October 2020|title=Maia Sandu, la lansarea în campanie: „Nu sunt perfectă, dar îmi pasă”. A ținut un discurs și în limba rusă|url=https://agora.md/stiri/77809/maia-sandu-la-lansarea-in-campanie-nu-sunt-perfecta-dar-imi-pasa-a-tinut-un-discurs-si-in-limba-rusa|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=|website=AGORA|language=ro}}</ref>, accusing president Dodon, of deliberately hindering the latter.<ref>{{Cite web|date=2020-10-08|title=Olesea Stamate a lansat Calendarul Injustiției: O retrospectivă a nedreptăților de la preluarea puterii de către Dodon|url=http://maiasandu2020.md/olesea-stamate-a-lansat-calendarul-injustitiei-o-retrospectiva-a-nedreptatilor-de-la-preluarea-puterii-de-catre-dodon/|access-date=2020-11-16|website=Maia Sandu Președinte 2020|language=ro-RO}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=2020-10-16|title=Flashmob la Președinție: Tinerii PAS i-au transmis lui Dodon ordinul „Gloria lenii”|url=http://maiasandu2020.md/flashmob-la-presedintie-tinerii-pas-i-au-transmis-lui-dodon-ordinul-gloria-lenii-2/|access-date=2020-11-16|website=Maia Sandu Președinte 2020|language=ro-RO}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=PAS il acuza pe Igor Dodon ca utilizeaza resursele administrative pentru a-si face campanie electorala - VIDEO|url=https://protv.md/politic/pas-il-acuza-pe-igor-dodon-ca-utilizeaza-resursele-administrative-pentru-a-si-face-campanie-electorala-video---2543482.html|access-date=2020-11-16|website=Pro TV|language=ro}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Borodin|first=Victoria|date=2020-09-07|title=Sandu îl acuză pe Dodon că încearcă să fure votul cetățenilor: „Va cheltui 2 milioane de euro pentru a cumpăra voturi din regiunea transnistreană”|url=https://cotidianul.md/2020/09/07/sandu-il-acuza-pe-dodon-ca-incearca-sa-fure-votul-cetatenilor-va-cheltui-2-milioane-de-euro-pentru-a-cumpara-voturi-din-regiunea-transnistreana/|access-date=2020-11-16|website=Cotidianul|language=ro-RO}}</ref> Because no candidate received a majority of votes in the first round, a run-off between Sandu and Dodon was held on 15 November, in which Sandu won with 57.75% of the popular vote.<ref name=":0">{{cite news |title=Moldova: Maia Sandu wins vote, beating Russia-backed competitor |url=https://www.msn.com/en-us/news/world/moldova-maia-sandu-wins-vote-beating-russia-backed-competitor/ar-BB1b3inF |accessdate=November 16, 2020 |work=msn.com |publisher=Al Jazeera English |date=November 16, 2020}}</ref><ref name=":1">{{cite news |title=Moldova's Dodon says concedes defeat in presidential runoff if courts find no violations |url=https://www.msn.com/en-us/news/world/moldovas-dodon-says-concedes-defeat-in-presidential-runoff-if-courts-find-no-violations/ar-BB1b3aV0 |accessdate=November 16, 2020 |work=msn.com |agency=Reuters |date=November 16, 2020}}</ref>
